=Hui Chao 慧超 (704-787)=
Korean Buddhist monk who went to China at young age, traveled to India by sea route and returned to China on the Silk routes. Probably never went back to Silla. 
==Works==
* 往五天竺國傳
==Literature==
===Translations===
* Yan Han-Sung: The Hye Ch'O Diary: Memoir of the Pilgrimage to the Five Regions of India. Berkeley: Asian Humanities Press, 1984.
===Articles===
* W. Fuchs: Pilgerreise durch Nordwest-Indien und Zentral-Asien um 726. Sitzungsberichten der Preußischen Akademie der Wissenschaften Phil.-hist. Klasse 30 (1938): 456-457